e\n(quenched) large deviation rate function, the prefactor exhibits a dependence\non the projection directions $(\\theta^n)_{n \\in\\mathbb{N}}$ that encodes\nadditional geometric information that enables one to distinguish between\nprojections of balls and spheres. Moreover, comparison with numerical estimates\nobtained by direct computation and importance sampling shows that the obtained\nanalytical expressions for tail probabilities provide good approximations even\nfor moderate values of $n$.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 13 Jan 2020 03:59:45 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 1 Sep 2020 07:25:15 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Thu, 28 Oct 2021 17:13:30 GMT"},{"version":"v4","created":"Sun, 23 Apr 2023 01:28:14 GMT"}],"update_date":"2023-04-25"}
