 the corresponding Lie-Cartan\nalgebra, as in other cases, but an irreducible central extension. When the\naction of the center of the annihilation algebra is trivial, this complex is\nrelated to work by M. Eastwood [E] on conformally symplectic geometry, and we\ncall it conformally symplectic pseudo de Rham complex.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 13 Jan 2020 08:40:06 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-01-14"}
